ters\nAfter Brisk Rally;\nAdvances Reduced\nBy th\u00ab Associated Press\nNEW YORK. Dec. 30.\u2014The stock\nmarket faltered today after a morn\ning advance.\nGains of fractions to around a\npoint were still in the majority, but\nthe widest advances had been\ntrimmed in many cases and some\nissues sliped into the minus column.\nNumerous big blocks of stock ap\npeared on the ticker tape although\noverall activity was only moderate.\nAmong the gainers were United\nStates Steel, National Steel, Pepsi\nCola, International Business Ma\nchines (at a 1948 high), RKO, Ad\nmiral Corp., Emerson Radio, Chrys\nler, Firestone, Caterpillar Tractor,\nMontgomery Ward. Consolidated\nNatural Gas, Anaconda Copper,\nWestinghouse Electric, Allied Chem\nical, Philip Morris, Southern Rail\nway, Nickel Plate and Standard Oil\nof New Jersey.\nMarked down a trifle were Bethle\nhem Steel, Goodrich, National Dis\ntillers, General Electric, Owens\nIllinois, Baltimore Ohio, Pan\nAmerican Airways, and Paramount\nPictures.\nHigher in the Curb were Cities\nService, Electric Bond Share,\nFairchild Engine, Pepperell and\nAtlas Plywood. General Plywood\nslipped, along with Wright Har\ngreaves and Raytheon Mfg.\nRailway bonds tended upward.\nUnited States Governments held\nfirm in over-the-counter dealings.\nProduce Markets\nBaltimore quotations furnished by the\nUnited States Department of Agriculture.\nAppIfs\u2014Market dull; bushel baskets and\nboxes. U. S. No. Is. 2\u2019/2-inch up. Pennsyl\nvania and Virginia Delicious. 2.50; Golden\nDelicious. 2.00-25; Romes. U. S Utility;\n2.50- 75; ,3-inch. 2.75-2.00; Staymans,\n2.50; Yorks 2.50-75; ,3-inch. 2.75-2.00;\nNew Jersey Paragons, 2.50-65; Stayman..\nfair quality and condition and poor color,\n2.75-3 00; Pennsylvania Golden Delicious,\n100-125s, 3.50-75: Staymans. SO-88s,\n3.50- 7 5\nPotatoes\u2014Market steady: lOo-pound\nsacks. U. S. No. Js. mostly size A Pennsyl\nvania Katahdins, uised sacks. 3.15-25,\nmostly 3.25-35; reprints. 3.35-40; new\nsacks